<subSubSection pageId="656" pageNumber="657" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="656" pageNumber="657">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelmatellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="656" pageNumber="657" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pelmatellus</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1882a: 68. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelmatellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="656" pageNumber="657" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">Pelmatellus nitescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1882 designated by Goulet (1974b: 84). Etymology. Possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">pelma</emphasis>
(sole of the foot) and the Latin 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">tellus</emphasis>
(earth) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="656" pageNumber="657" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="656" pageNumber="657">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="656" pageNumber="657">
Twenty-eight species in the Nearctic (two species) and Neotropical (28 species) Regions arrayed in three subgenera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrault" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelmatellopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="656" pageNumber="657" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">Pelmatellopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Perrault (17 South American species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelmatellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="656" pageNumber="657" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">Pelmatellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (10 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Thenarellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="656" pageNumber="657" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="656" pageNumber="657">Thenarellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates (one Middle American species).
</paragraph>
